rComments: She was great! Definitely not an easy grader, and you'll have to study, but expectations are clear. There is a good amount of additional work (graded tutorials, quizzes) but in theory, that time replaces extra time you would have spent studying anyway, and boosts grades. Definitely cares about students and improving the course.

Terrible prof as she does not give fair exams or midterms and will absolutely not bell curve under any circumstances. Not good at teaching the material nor does she really care about the performance of her students. Should not be teaching a class as important as this one.

I've had Professor Fauteux-Lefebvre twice in my degree and I'm frankly surprised by the reviews here. She is one of the most caring professors that I've had in university and she's always available to help her students. For CHG2717, just do the work/assignments and you'll do fine.
Very nice person, and a good teacher. The fill-in-the-blank slides (having to annotate PDF files..) and blended learning were a bit of a pain.

Terrible professor, exams do not reflect was is covered in the course. The tutorials are completely useless, it just flares up your anxiety. Class is hard as it is, and she makes it worst. Avoid at all costs.

Elle veut vraiment voir ses élèves réussir. Elle s'assure que la classe comprend avant d'avencer dans la matière. Les devoirs et numéros d'exercices préparent bien pour les examens. Assurez vous de comprendre les devoirs et tout ira bien (elle est aussi extr ;)
